The First-Ever ASMR Cover
COSMO × PORUS VIMADALAL (@porus.vimadalal) &
PRAYAG MENON (@prayag.menon)

Cosmo: Porus, what sounds are soothing to you?

Porus Vimadalal: “The sound of birds chirping...which heralds the beginning of a new day, the gentle rustling of leaves as trees sway in the breeze, the sound of heavy rain, and even classical music has a calming effect on the mind.”

C: And how do you spend your free time?

PV: “I enjoy cooking. it helps me unwind. I also spend time nurturing my plants, as it gives me a sense of fulfilment to watch them grow and flourish. Prayag and I often exercise together, and enjoy a weekend ritual of dinner and a movie date at home.“

Cosmo: Prayag, tell us about your hobbies...

Prayag Menon: “I enjoy reading articles on genetic testing and historical features. I also engage with Reddit gossip threads as I binge eat in the comfort of my bed. It’s my way of indulging [laughs]. Plus, I love planning adventurous getaways for Porus and me..it’s so exciting.”

C: And how was your experience shooting for the first-ever ASMR cover?

PM: “The entire creative experience was immersive and super-fun... I love how the concept of this ASMR cover perfectly aligned with Porus and my artistic vision.

On that rare occasion when @prayag.menon is feeling generous enough to photograph me; I must oblige.

#TalesofCusrowBaug - A photo essay in collaboration with @prayag.menon and @ashdeenl, the designer behind the beautiful handmade ghara sarees, with a passion for reviving the art, is a step into the timeless embrace of Cusrow Baug; a Parsi colony nestled in the heart of Colaba since the 1930s, with some of its residents as old as the colony itself. Amidst the labyrinth lanes, and lush gardens, tradition and modernity dance hand in hand. The air resonates with the scent of homemade Parsi delicacies and each doorstep tells a story, adorned with “torans” (garlands) made of glass beads and “chalk” (rangoli), signifying a deep-rooted devotion to customs.

Model: @vahishtaz
Makeup/Hair: @arshisjaveriofficial

#TalesofCusrowBaug - As the senior editor of Parsiana magazine, Farrokh Jijina’s house is a treasure trove of history and cherished memories, filled with furniture across eras that carry multi-generational stories. As the afternoon sun bathes the interior, delicate lace curtains sway in the gentle breeze, art deco furniture from the 60s and 70s adorns the living room, while Victorian style chairs, from his parents' wedding, stand as nostalgic heirlooms.

Cusrow Baug, where Farrokh has been a resident all his life, holds a special place in his heart, best described as "Heaven on Earth." One fascinating aspect he mentions is the coolness at the gates even during the peak of summer. His mother used to refer to this phenomenon as "Jerbai na aashirwad," perhaps attributing the comforting atmosphere to some form of divine blessing. The massive peepal tree in the neighbouring Badhwar Park, with its generous branches extending towards his house, offers a delightful sight. Farrokh mentions how he cherishes waking up to the symphony of birdsong accompanying this view every morning. 

It's evident that he has a deep emotional connection with this place, one which holds countless memories as well as stories that have shaped his life and made his living experience truly unique, truly remarkable.

#TalesofCusrowBaug - Meet Nergish Phiroze Charna, a remarkable soul who has called Cusrow Baug home throughout her entire life, witnessing her many milestones and creating unforgettable memories.

From her prestigious role as the Principal of Elphinstone College to being a guiding force in the University of Mumbai Academic Council and Chairperson of the Board of Studies in Political Science, Nergish has created an enduring legacy.

"Cusrow Baug's location is a dream come true! With everything close by, from schools to theaters, commuting has always been a breeze," she fondly recalls.

Retirement opened a new chapter for Nergish, as she discovered a passion for tailoring. Her home now doubles as a haven for creativity, where she lovingly crafts clothes for friends and family.

As we stepped into her abode, we were captivated by the timeless allure of her surroundings, adorned with beautiful furniture and cherished antiques. "No matter where I travel, my heart yearns for Cusrow Baug. It's more than home; it's a part of who I am." she confides.

#TalesofCusrowBaug - One of the notable landmarks of Cusrow Baug is its iconic main gate, which holds historical significance and serves as a symbol of the colony's identity.

This photo essay, in collaboration with @prayag.menon and @ashdeenl, captures the essence of this vibrant community, where every corner tells a story of cherished memories and unyielding nostalgia. It's a close-knit neighborhood where people often know each other well and share a strong sense of community and camaraderie.

Cusrow Baug is more than just a residential colony; it's a living testament to the Parsi community's preservation of their cultural identity in the bustling metropolis of Mumbai.

For my 38th birthday today, Prayag planned something truly special – a stay at The Oberoi Grand in Kolkata; a property I spent many blissful summer holidays with my family. The last time I was here was with my dad on one of his final flights 13 years ago, just a few months before we lost him. This is where I learned to swim, relished hearty club sandwiches and fish and chips in bed, and indulged in countless movies on VCR! 30+ years later, it’s still the same. This trip is immensely nostalgic for me, and it’s the perfect way to celebrate my birthday. 🎂 ♥️

Image 1: A portrait of me by @prayag.menon on the balcony of @theoberoigrandkolkata 

Image 2: Me and my sister on one of the hotel’s balcony some 30+ years ago!
